      • isFailed

        boolean isFailed()
        Returns if the test case is failed. This can also be true if the test case is ignored; in this case, the status will be IGNORED , but as the test may still have been executed (e.g. AludraTest does this), this flag here can be used to determine the execution success.
        Returns:
        true if the test case execution was unsuccessful, false otherwise.
